We are using **WaveSurfer.js v7** (React/TypeScript version) in this project.

### API Reference Links
- **Options**: https://wavesurfer.xyz/docs/types/wavesurfer.WaveSurferOptions
- **Events**: https://wavesurfer.xyz/docs/types/wavesurfer.WaveSurferEvents
- **Main Documentation**: https://wavesurfer.xyz/docs/

### Key Differences from v6
- TypeScript rewrite with better type safety
- HTML5 audio playback by default (no Web Audio backend)
- Enhanced performance and new plugin system
- `seekAndCenter` method removed - use `autoCenter` and `autoScroll` options instead
- Region highlighting must be done via CSS manipulation, not built-in methods

### Important Options for Our Use Case
- `autoCenter: boolean` - Keep cursor centered during playback
- `autoScroll: boolean` - Auto-scroll to keep current position in viewport
- `minPxPerSec: number` - Zoom level (pixels per second)
- `interact: boolean` - Enable/disable waveform interactions

### Region Plugin
- Import: `import Regions from 'wavesurfer.js/dist/plugins/regions.esm.js'`
- Regions have `color`, `resize`, `drag` properties
- Use `regionsPlugin.getRegions()` to access regions
- Region events: `region-in`, `region-out`, `region-clicked`, `region-updated`

### Best Practices
- Always wait for `ready` event before manipulating waveform
- Use `seekTo(progress)` where progress is 0-1 (not time in seconds)
- For centering, combine `seekTo` with `autoCenter: true` option
- Handle browser autoplay restrictions gracefully
